#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn1.54"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn1.54:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 1 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 1 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn1.54:0.2"
msgid "6. Jarāvagga "
msgstr "6. Old Age "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn1.54:0.3"
msgid "54. Vatthusutta "
msgstr "54. Grounds "

# NOTE: I think the underlying metaphor here is more concrete than “support”: it is a person’s lands, their property, which is their support and legacy. As usual, the Buddha’s response aims to upend conventional values.
#. HTML: </h1></div><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn1.54:1.1"
msgid "“Kiṃsu vatthu manussānaṃ, "
msgstr "“What is the ground of human beings? "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.54:1.2"
msgid "kiṃsūdha paramo sakhā; "
msgstr "What is the best companion here? "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.54:1.3"
msgid "Kiṃsu bhūtā upajīvanti, "
msgstr "By what do the creatures who live off the earth "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: pathavissitā”ti → paṭhaviṃ sitāti (bj, s1-3, km, pts2) | pathaviṃ sitāti (pts1)
msgctxt "sn1.54:1.4"
msgid "ye pāṇā pathavissitā”ti. "
msgstr "sustain their life?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn1.54:2.1"
msgid "“Puttā vatthu manussānaṃ, "
msgstr "“Children are the ground of human beings. "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: bhariyā ca → bhariyāva (bj, pts2) | bhariyā (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn1.54:2.2"
msgid "bhariyā ca paramo sakhā; "
msgstr "A wife is the best companion. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.54:2.3"
msgid "Vuṭṭhiṃ bhūtā upajīvanti, "
msgstr "The creatures who live off the earth "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.54:2.4"
msgid "ye pāṇā pathavissitā”ti. "
msgstr "sustain their life by rain.”"

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
